class Solution {
    public long minEnd(int n, int x) {
        n--;
        long result = x;
        long mask = 1L;
        while ((n & ~0L) != 0) {
            if ((x & mask) == 0) {
                if ((n & 1) != 0) {
                    result |= mask;
                }
                n >>>= 1;
            }
            mask <<= 1;
        }
        return result;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n + log x)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution constructs the minimum possible last element of the array by distributing the bits of n-1 into the available positions in x, ensuring the bitwise AND operation between all elements results in x.
